International Business Machines Corp Announces 10-Year Strategic Partnership With UniCredit to Deliver New Services
Thursday, 18 Jul 2013 08:00am EDT
International Business Machines Corp (IBM) announced a multi-billion dollar, 10-year agreement to transform the IT infrastructure that supports all of UniCredit's commercial and private banking activities in Europe. The agreement will include the creation of a joint venture between UniCredit Business Integrated Solutions - the global service company of UniCredit - and IBM, which will have employees in Italy, Germany, Austria, Slovakia, and Czech Republic of both companies. As part of the agreement, the company will market and deliver IT infrastructure services not only to UniCredit, but also to other companies and institutions.Â 
